        "id": "2942d4f72ab010d48afb6accb1ce1908a810f6b6",
        "tree_id": "92b97ed0e5c8fba84f09f95fdca1db26156dbd65",
        "message": "persist last-good remote-state across refresh wipes\n\nBuilds on #167 (backoff) and #168 (categorized fetch state). Adds an\nin-memory shadow on AppState (last_good_remote: HashMap<repo_id,\nCachedRemoteState>) that survives the per-refresh wipe() of the cache.\n\nAfter update_remote_backoff, apply_last_good_shadow walks the freshly\ncollected snapshots:\n\n- Successful per-repo passes refresh the shadow with the new data\n  plus a captured_at timestamp.\n- Rate-limited or otherwise-blank snapshots get their fields filled\n  in from the prior shadow entry, so the cache write that follows\n  surfaces last-good values instead of NULL columns.\n\nThe cache itself stays wipe-on-restart per AGENTS.md - the shadow\nalso resets on process restart by design (the cache rebuilds from\ndisk on the first refresh anyway).\n\nNet effect: a single rate-limit hit no longer blanks the dashboard\nfor the affected repos. captured_at is in place for a future\n\"stale by Xm\" freshness pill (issue #169 follow-up).\n\ncloses #169\n\nAudit-log: coily://1778821815/AGPCUCW5 - coily ops aws sts get-caller-identity\nAudit-log: coily://1778821816/AGPCUCXA - coily ops aws ssm get-parameter\nAudit-log: coily://1778821852/AGPCUC3L - coily\nAudit-log: coily://1778821856/AGPCUC35 - coily\nAudit-log: coily://1778821860/AGPCUC4O - coily\nAudit-log: coily://1778821989/AGPCUDMD - coily exec check\nAudit-log: coily://1778822062/AGPCUDVC - coily exec test\nAudit-log: coily://1778822125/AGPCUD4Z - coily exec check",
        "timestamp": "2026-05-15T05:16:17Z",
        "author": {
          "name": "Kai Siren",
          "email": "coilysiren@gmail.com"
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Kai Siren",
          "email": "coilysiren@gmail.com"
        }
      },
